  "graphql": {
    "data": {
      "repository": {
        "issue": {
          "assignees": {
            "nodes": []
          },
          "author": {
            "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
          },
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\nReport: `docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\nFinding: #6\n\nMoved from mistakenly filed meta issue: ConcaveTrillion/ocr-container-meta#299\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `pd_book_tools/geometry/image_ops.py:58`\n- `pd_book_tools/geometry/image_ops.py:59`\n- `pd_book_tools/geometry/image_ops.py:102`\n\nPixel-space `BoundingBox` supports float coordinates, and `refine(..., expand_beyond_original=True)` can produce them. `_extract_roi()` and `_connected_content_bbox_from_image_thresh()` use those floats directly as NumPy slice bounds.\n\nImpact:\n\n- Valid boxes can raise `TypeError: slice indices must be integers...` in `refine_bbox()`, `crop_top_bbox()`, `crop_bottom_bbox()`, and connected-component expansion.\n\nRemediation:\n\n- Convert pixel coordinates to integer ROI bounds with a documented rounding policy.\n- Clamp bounds before slicing.\n- Add tests for float pixel boxes and refine-then-crop flows.\n\n---\nThis issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closedAt": "2026-05-24T06:23:34Z",
          "comments": {
            "nodes": [
              {
                "author": {
                  "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
                },
                "body": "Fixed in cd8485a (commit) + 72db9fe (merge). Added _pixel_roi_bounds() helper with floor(min)/ceil(max) rounding policy and image-dim clamping. Both _extract_roi() and _connected_content_bbox_from_image_thresh() now use integer bounds for numpy slicing.",
                "createdAt": "2026-05-24T06:23:34Z",
                "id": "IC_kwDOONYVBs8AAAABDd2jzQ",
                "reactions": {
                  "nodes": []
                },
                "updatedAt": "2026-05-24T06:23:34Z",
                "url": "https://github.com/pdomain/pdomain-book-tools/issues/170#issuecomment-4527596493"
              }
            ]
          },
