          "author_association": "OWNER",
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\n    Report: `pd-book-tools/docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\n    Finding: #6\n\n    ## Summary\n\n    Valid pixel-space BoundingBox instances can contain float coordinates, but bbox image ops use them directly as NumPy slice bounds.\n\n    ## Impact\n\n    refine_bbox(), crop_top_bbox(), crop_bottom_bbox(), and connected-component expansion can crash with TypeError.\n\n    ## Evidence\n\n    - `pd_book_tools/geometry/image_ops.py:58`\n- `pd_book_tools/geometry/image_ops.py:59`\n- `pd_book_tools/geometry/image_ops.py:102`\n\n    ## Acceptance\n\n    - [ ] Convert pixel coordinates to integer ROI bounds with documented rounding.\n- [ ] Clamp before slicing.\n- [ ] Add tests for float pixel boxes and refine-then-crop flows.\n\n    ## Notes\n\n    This issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closed_at": "2026-05-22T16:03:48Z",
